# Configuration file for the "Sage" background

# Personality Trait				bg[0] 
I use polysyllabic words that convey the impression of great erudition.::I've read every book in the world's greatest libraries- or I like to boast that I have.::I'm used to helping out those who aren't as smart as I am, and I patiently explain anything to others.::There's nothing I like ore than a good mystery.::I'm willing to listen to every side of an argument before I make my own judgment.::I...speak...slowly...when talking...to idiots,...which...almost...everyone...is...compared...to me.::I am horribly, horribly awkward in social situations.::I'm convinced that people are always trying to steal my secrets.

# Ideals						bg[1]
Knowledge: The path to power and self-improvement is through knowledge. (Neutral)::Beauty: What is beautiful points us beyond itself toward what is true. (Good)::Logic: Emotions should fetter the infinate possibility inherent in all existance. (Chaotic)::Power: Knowledge is the path to power and domination. (Evil)::S

# Bonds							bg[2]
It is my duty to protect my students.::I have an ancient text that holds terribly secrets that must not fall into the wrong hands.::I work to preserve a library, university, scriptorium, or monastery.::My life's work is a series of tomes related to a specific field of lore.::I've been searching my whole life for the answer to a certain question.::I sold my soul for knowledge. I hope to do great deeds and win in back.

# Flaws							bg[3
I am easily distracted by the promise of information.::Most people scream and run when they see a deamon. I stop and take notes on its anatomy.::Unlocking and ancient mystery is worth the price of a civilization.::I overlook obvious solutions in favor of complicated ones.::I speak without really thinking my words, invariably insulting others.::I can't keep a secret to save my life, or anyone else's.

# Speacialty 					bg[4]
Alchemist::Astronomer::Discredited academic::Librarian::Professor::Researcher::Wizard's apprentice::Scribe
